{
  "text": "In summary, we propose an on-chip bimetallic plasmo thermomechanical mid-IR detector that uses waveguided modes to detect IR incident wave through the evanescent field modulation. The design is scalable and can be applied to wavelengths from mid-IR to near-IR, i.e., detecting 785 nm [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12359280"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "12359280": {
      "title": "Infrared detection using plasmonically enhanced thermomechanically actuated nanowire arrays",
      "abstract": "A plasmo-thermomechanical IR detector based on suspended bilayer nanowire array is demonstrated. The detector exhibits an absorption coefficient of 0.0494. The maximum difference in S 21 between the radiation on and off states is 0.013 with a radiation intensity of 0.1 mW/μm2."
    }
  }
}